Class Tangible

java.lang.Object
  java.util.Observable
      edu.ucsd.ccdb.ontomorph2.core.scene.tangible.Tangible
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
Axon, BrainRegion, Curve3D, CurveAnchorPoint, DataMesh, MorphMLCableImpl, MorphMLSegmentImpl, NeuroMLNetwork, NeuronMorphology, QueryResults, SchematicTangible, Slide, Surface, Volume
public abstract class Tangible
extends java.util.Observable
implements ISemanticsAware

Defines an object that can be viewed in the scene. This object can be made relative to an arbitrary coordinate system.

Author:
Stephen D. Larson (slarson@ncmir.ucsd.edu)
See Also:

rotate

public void rotate(float dx,
                   float dy,
                   OMTVector constraint)
Changes the rotation of this Tangible

Parameters:
morph - the item(s) to be rotated
constraint - the axis (or axes) on which to rotate the object. For example, if constraint is (1,0,0) the object will rotates about it's own X axis (not the world's X axis)

move

public void move(float dx,
                 float dy,
                 OMTVector constraint)
Changes the local translation this Tangible The dimensions of freedom allow the 2D movement of the mouse to map to the 3D movement intended

Parameters:
constraint - Specifies what dimensions to allow movement based on mouse input. Will typically range from (0,0,0) to (1,1,1). Where (1,1,0) corresponds to 2D movement on the current X,Y plane
